Instead, to suit their own desires, they will gather around them a great number of teachers to say what their itching ears want to hear. I've read quite a few comments and for anyone who has the guts to read this pay attention to the scripture above. People somehow, someway have the notion that you can be a good person, with a good character,  with a good heart, and this will get you in heaven. You can be the type of person that gives money to worthy causes, you can be a person that inspires people, or you can have a special ability rather if it's singing, or an athlete or a exceptional business mind making large sums of money and this will get you in heaven. That's what the 'itching ears' reference means. 'Sound Doctrine' says that Jesus is the only way to the Father. That you must ask Jesus to come into your life, be the savior of your soul, the Lord of your life, and then you must do your best to live holy.That means spending time with him, rather if its in church or reading your bible so that you won't be fooled by false teachings.
